html.body: WEE1 module WEE1 locates in the nucleus where it phosphorylates and inactivates different forms of CycB1/CDC2 (PMID:8348613). CDC25C can be found in the cytoplasm and in the nucleus and activates the complex (PMID:10373560; 9001210; PMID:12814430). CDC25C responds to DNA damage via the phosphorylation by CHEK1 and CHEK2 (PMID:12478465). The phosphorylated CDC25C is then exported to the cytoplasm preventing the activation of nuclear CycB1/CDC2 (PMID:12814430). CDC25C activity is low during interphase and high during mitosis whereas WEE1 activity has an opposite behaviour.
